sentences: Frederikke Hoffmeier (born 1989), better known by her stage name Puce Mary, is a Danish experimental musician, composer and sound artist.
Frederikke Hoffmeier was born in 1989 in Denmark.
Her debut release under the name Puce Mary, Piss Flowers, was issued in cassette format in 2010.
Her debut full-length album, Success, was released in 2013 on Posh Isolation record label.
The record was followed up by 2014's Persona.
In 2015, Hoffmeier collaborated with Rahbek on the full-length release, The Female Form.
Her 2018 album, The Drought, was released on Berlin-based record label PAN and received positive reviews from publications such as Pitchfork, Resident Advisor and The Quietus.
In 2020, she scored the film Kød & Blod, which was directed by Jeanette Nordahl.

The following year saw the release of her fourth solo studio album, The Spiral.
In the same year, she contributed to the track "Hope in Suffering (Escaping Oblivion & Overcoming Powerlessness)" by Yves Tumor, released on their album Safe in the Hands of Love.
